class Solution {
    public String largestPalindrome(int n, int k) {
        int maxDigits = (int) Math.ceil(Math.sqrt(k));
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        for (int i = maxDigits; i >= n; i--) {
            sb.append(k % 10);
            k /= 10;
        }
        return sb.reverse().toString();
    }
}
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

The solution iterates from the maximum number of digits that can be formed using k (sqrt(k)) down to n. For each digit, it appends the remainder of k divided by 10 to the StringBuilder, updates k by dividing it by 10, and continues until reaching n. Finally, it reverses the StringBuilder and returns the result as a string. This approach ensures that the resulting number has exactly n digits and is a k-palindrome.

